.head 4 +  Functions
.head 5 +  Function: FormChildrenLoop
.head 6 -  Description: Performs a loop through the children of the hWndFrmHdl, sending message nPAM_CHILDACTION
to each child with nMSG_wParam and nMSG_lParam as wParam and lParam to each child.
The type of children is determined by paramenter nType which should be constanst TYPE_....
nStopOnReturnValue is the value that a error will be detected on and loop terminated.
For a case like DATAVAL being sent around then FALSE should be nStopOnReturnValue to force
each child to trap that message.
.head 6 +  Returns
.head 7 -  Boolean:
.head 6 +  Parameters
.head 7 -  Window Handle: hWndFrmHdl
.head 7 -  Number: nPAM_CHILDACTION
.head 7 -  Number: nMSG_wParam
.head 7 -  Number: nMSG_lParam
.head 7 -  Number: nType
.head 7 -  Number: nStopOnReturnValue
.head 6 -  Static Variables
.head 6 +  Local variables
.head 7 -  Window Handle: hWndChild
.head 7 -  Number: nActionReturn
.head 7 -  Boolean: bError
.head 6 +  Actions
.head 7 -  Call OurWaitCursor( TRUE )
.head 7 -  Set bError = FALSE
.head 7 -  !
.head 7 -  Set hWndChild = SalGetFirstChild( hWndFrmHdl, nType )
.head 7 +  While hWndChild != hWndNULL
.head 8 -  Set nActionReturn = SalSendMsg( hWndChild, nPAM_CHILDACTION, nMSG_wParam, nMSG_lParam )
.head 8 +  If nActionReturn = nStopOnReturnValue
.head 9 -  Set bError = TRUE
.head 9 -  Break
.head 8 +  Else
.head 9 -  Set hWndChild = SalGetNextChild( hWndChild, nType )
.head 7 -  !
.head 7 -  Call OurWaitCursor( FALSE )
.head 7 +  If bError
.head 8 -  Return FALSE
.head 7 +  Else
.head 8 -  Return TRUE
